cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CL 

This paper presents a framework for predicting affordances of object parts of unseen categories, with application to robot manipulation. The paper focuses on computer vision and robotics, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) sub-categories. The paper also uses deep learning techniques, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The paper uses a self-attention mechanism and an auxiliary task of object attribute inference, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves segmentation and detection of objects, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category.
